– Armor Class: +1 vs. missiles and piercing weapons
– Immunity to "Summon Insects" and "Insect Plague"

Weight: 3~
@1207 = ~This emerald-hued rose is a gift from Mythrien Sarath, the Watcher over Mythals. Each of its fragile petals glimmers with a light not of this world, as though echoing the lost wards of ancient elven cities.
When a petal is plucked, a translucent sphere surrounds the bearer, shielding <PRO_HIMHER> from spells of lesser potency. Yet the gift is fleeting—when the last petal falls, the rose will crumble to dust.

STATISTICS:

Charge abilities:
– Pluck a Petal: Grants immunity to spells of up to 5th level for 3 rounds
– Limited number of uses; the rose vanishes when depleted

Weight: 0~
@1208 = ~Elminster's Ecologies: Appendix IVa~
@1209 = ~Elminster's Ecologies: Appendix IVa

This time-worn tome is written by the sage Elminster, and apparently part of a much larger body of work containing detailed studies of most of the strange creatures from around Faerûn. 

The appendix seems to refer to newly-discovered variations on normal breeds of creatures. Of particular interest:

"Will-o’-the-Wisps (Common)
These pale, floating lights haunt marshes and ruins, feeding on fear. They lure travelers astray and strike with crackling bursts of lightning. Hard to harm with steel or spell, they remain among the most treacherous of minor undead."

"Will-o’Wild
A mutation born of unstable magic. Flickering in ever-changing flashes, these lights twist spells around them—wards collapse, surges erupt, enchantments go awry. They are most often found drifting in regions of wild magic."

"Will-o’Dead
Spawn of the lifeless Weave, these wan globes feed not on fear, but on life force. They linger where magic itself has failed — in the barren places known as dead-magic zones."~
@1210 = ~Essence of the Will-o’Dead~
@1211 = ~A faintly glowing mote of pallid light, cold to the touch and unnervingly silent. Lore-whispers suggest that such an essence could one day serve to counter the emptiness where the Weave has failed.~
@1212 = ~Essence of the Will-o’Wild~
@1213 = ~This shimmering fragment pulses with chaotic hues, shifting from emerald to amber in an instant. It carries within it the untamed spark of wild magic, unpredictable yet potent. Some claim that such essence, properly bound, might shield its bearer from the turbulence of unstable Weave-fields.~ 
@1214 = ~Manual of Peaceful Living~
@1215 = ~Manual of Peaceful Living
This contemplative tome  offers guidance on living a life of serenity and restraint. As with all such rare works, the book vanishes after a single use.

STATISTICS:

Attacks per Round: Reduced by 0.5 (permanently)
Armor Class: Improved by 1 (permanently)
Saving Throws: +1 bonus (permanently)
Special: The book is consumed upon use
Usage: Place into quick item slot

Weight: 25~
@1216 = ~Fairy Jar~
@1217 = ~This crystal jar contains two tiny winged creatures - the Dell-Light Twins, the two fairies from Duskwood Dell, apparently. They appear fully conscious, peering out with curious eyes, their lips moving as if in constant conversation — though no sound escapes. The jar’s lid refuses to move, sealed by a magic older and subtler than any lock. Occasionally, one of the twins presses her hands against the inside, mouthing words the glass will not let through. Whether plea or mischief, it’s impossible to tell.

The seal cannot be opened or broken by physical or magical means. The faeries within are alive but imprisoned, their magic suppressed by the vessel’s binding.

Weight: 1~
@1218 = ~Mirage’s Edge~
@1219 = ~Forged by genies who sought to weave illusion and motion into one, this blade can wrap its wielder in shimmering reflections — turning the swordsman into a living mirage.

